FBIS3-23113 "jptot010__l94076" JPRS-TOT-94-010-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 10 March 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA IRAN Opposition Leader Escapes Murder Attempt in Florence BR2802094094 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1841 GMT 27 Feb 93 BR2802094094 Rome ANSAMAIL Database Language: English Article Type:BFN [Unattributed article: "Iran Opposition Leader Reported Attacked in Florence"] [Text] Nicosia, 27 Feb (ANSA) -- The Iranian National Resistance Council said that one of its members in Florence escaped an assassination attempt yesterday. In a statement to ANSA's Nicosia bureau, the group said that "two terrorists sent by the Khomeyni regime" chased one of their members in a car. The two, arrested by Tuscan police, were identified by the opposition group as Ayoub Fayoui and Iraj Oaderi [names as received]. Last March, an opposition leader Mohammed Hossein Naghdidel [name as received] was assassinated in Rome.
